[3] Hawaii
Date: Fri 10 Nov 2017
Source: DG Alerts, State Health Agency; Student Health Services report [edited]
http://dgalerts.docguide.com/hi-ny-dc-usa-mumps-update-500-cases-hi?nl_ref=newsletter&pk_campaign=newsletter


The Hawaii State Department of Health (DOH) continues to investigate an increasing number of cases of mumps infection statewide.

The disease has been confirmed in children and adults, both vaccinated and unvaccinated. Nearly 60 percent of cases have been in adults aged 18 years and older. There have been 16 reports of complications due to mumps infection (such as, orchitis, hearing loss).

As of 9 Nov 2017, there have been 557 confirmed cases of mumps for 2017, with the distribution of cases as follows:
- Honolulu 450
- Hawaii 61
- Kauai 44
- Maui 2

Due to the current mumps outbreak in Hawaii, in addition to the routine vaccination recommendations above, persons born in 1957 or later, especially those who live or work in crowded conditions, should receive an additional MMR vaccine dose now.

